<font color="#FF0000">ONE MESSAGE FOR SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec  3 23:31:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
spatz<br><br>
I have conversed with you the longest of those who now write here, but I stopped responding a while back in order to try to make some sense of this.  Your responses are senseless to me.  Now, you say I've made some good points about language.  Do you remember how many times I've said the same thing over the last year?  It has to be at least five other times!  You did not respond then, and I expect you to &quot;loose it&quot; again.  That has been your excuse over the last year.  <br><br>
You have finally met some people who refuse to acknowledge that your words make sense, and have called you for what you have demonstrated time and again--that you have no ethics or morality when it comes to putting down Vietnam Vets.<br><br>
I wrote a post to you a while back and asked some pointed questions.  You never answered, even though I re-posted the questions several times.  &quot;How can our country benefit from our experiences and commitment to each other that we exhibited in 'Nam?&quot;  This question was posted on Thread #125, &quot;Good Night Vietnam Site&quot; on October 19, 1997.  Instead, you continued and escalated your war of words with several other people, to the point where they became nauseating and extremely repugnant.  <br><br>
Now, you want to begin anew...NO SUCH DEAL!  In order to have any kind of credibility, you will have to make a BIG, BIG CHANGE.  It will have to be obvious to us too.  I, for one, don't know if there is any hope that you can do anything to change our perceptions of you.  <br><br>
Your expressions of hate towards us are the personification of some of the most dark, underlying nightmares we have had over the last 25 years of how a very few Americans see Vietnam Veterans.  But those few still cause us a lot of grief.  You, at least, have now shown that this is not a figment of our imagination, that real people do have these thoughts, and that we have had to contend with this for over 25 years.  You may not be unique, but that doesn't lessen the transgressions.<br>

<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


